{
    "publish_date": "2013-01-10T17:52:51.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT11M52S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: This is such an\ninspiring story, because it", 
            "dur": "4.618", 
            "start": "1.992"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "shows how mathematicians\ncan save lives.", 
            "dur": "4.39", 
            "start": "6.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;re talking about one of\nthe most famous cipher", 
            "dur": "2.88", 
            "start": "11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "machines of all time.", 
            "dur": "1.33", 
            "start": "13.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s a code machine called the\nEnigma machine used by Nazi", 
            "dur": "3.14", 
            "start": "15.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Germany in World War II to send\nsecret, coded messages.", 
            "dur": "4.1", 
            "start": "18.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we&#39;ve got one over here.", 
            "dur": "2.19", 
            "start": "22.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is not a copy.", 
            "dur": "0.965", 
            "start": "24.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is not a replica.", 
            "dur": "1.755", 
            "start": "25.605"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is an original Enigma\nmachine actually used", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "27.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in World War II.", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "30.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This was made in 1936.", 
            "dur": "2.16", 
            "start": "32.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s an army Enigma machine.", 
            "dur": "2.18", 
            "start": "34.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s see how it works.", 
            "dur": "1.12", 
            "start": "36.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this belongs to a man\ncalled Simon Singh.", 
            "dur": "3.4", 
            "start": "37.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He&#39;s an author.", 
            "dur": "1.03", 
            "start": "40.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He writes popular\nscience books.", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "41.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he lends it to\nthe University of", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "44.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Cambridge, where I work.", 
            "dur": "1.44", 
            "start": "46.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This was found in a French\nfield, I was told, by an", 
            "dur": "3.99", 
            "start": "48.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "American cryptographer\nafter the war.", 
            "dur": "2.33", 
            "start": "52.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he took it home.", 
            "dur": "1.04", 
            "start": "54.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I guess he took it home\nas his souvenir.", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "55.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Yoink, that&#39;s mine.", 
            "dur": "1.11", 
            "start": "57.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The guy who found it died\nabout 12 years ago.", 
            "dur": "3.77", 
            "start": "58.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when he died, that&#39;s\nwhen Simon", 
            "dur": "1.95", 
            "start": "62.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Singh bought the machine.", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "64.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;re going to send a message.", 
            "dur": "1.01", 
            "start": "66.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, we were talking about what\nto send before, so we", 
            "dur": "2.75", 
            "start": "67.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "send Numberphile.", 
            "dur": "0.91", 
            "start": "70.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s turn this into\nEnigma code.", 
            "dur": "3.08", 
            "start": "71.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;m going to type\nin N to begin with.", 
            "dur": "2.59", 
            "start": "74.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if you can see there,\nthe letter Y lights up.", 
            "dur": "2.47", 
            "start": "76.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So N becomes Y. Your\ncode lights up.", 
            "dur": "2.48", 
            "start": "79.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s write that down.", 
            "dur": "1.19", 
            "start": "81.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s do the next letter, U. U\nbecomes T. Let&#39;s do M. And", 
            "dur": "6.22", 
            "start": "82.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ve got H this time.", 
            "dur": "1.77", 
            "start": "89.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "B. And E is W.", 
            "dur": "7.04", 
            "start": "90.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Notice here, we had\nY turn up twice.", 
            "dur": "4.58", 
            "start": "97.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And they turned up for two\ndifferent letters.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "102.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So N became Y, and\nthen later on, E", 
            "dur": "2.62", 
            "start": "104.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "became Y. That&#39;s unusual.", 
            "dur": "1.46", 
            "start": "107.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The other unusual thing you may\nnotice is that the two E&#39;s", 
            "dur": "3.57", 
            "start": "108.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in Numberphile have turned into\ntwo different letters.", 
            "dur": "3.38", 
            "start": "112.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So here, E became Y. But\nthe second E became W.", 
            "dur": "4.45", 
            "start": "115.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, this is why the Germans\nthought they had an", 
            "dur": "2.08", 
            "start": "120.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "unbreakable code.", 
            "dur": "1.25", 
            "start": "122.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Old-fashioned code in the past,\npen-and-paper codes that", 
            "dur": "3.69", 
            "start": "123.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they used to use, if you had\nthe same letter, it would", 
            "dur": "3.1", 
            "start": "127.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "become the same letter\nin the code.", 
            "dur": "2.85", 
            "start": "130.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Enigma is different.", 
            "dur": "1.28", 
            "start": "133.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Probably, each time you did it,\nyou would get a completely", 
            "dur": "3.05", 
            "start": "134.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "different code.", 
            "dur": "1.53", 
            "start": "137.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, if we can break this code--\nand by we, I mean the", 
            "dur": "2.99", 
            "start": "138.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Polish, the British,\nand the Americans--", 
            "dur": "3.09", 
            "start": "141.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if we can break this code in\nWorld War II, we&#39;ll be able to", 
            "dur": "3.69", 
            "start": "144.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "read those German\nsecret messages,", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "148.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is what we did.", 
            "dur": "1.21", 
            "start": "151.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So let me show you how\nthis machine works.", 
            "dur": "1.81", 
            "start": "152.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let me open up the machine.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "154.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we have three things\nhere at the top.", 
            "dur": "3.14", 
            "start": "156.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These things are\ncalled rotors.", 
            "dur": "1.51", 
            "start": "159.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And inside those rotors, try\nand imagine lots of wiring.", 
            "dur": "3.46", 
            "start": "160.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s all crisscrossed\nwiring as well.", 
            "dur": "2.39", 
            "start": "164.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, if I press a letter, have\na look what happens.", 
            "dur": "2.255", 
            "start": "166.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The rotors move.", 
            "dur": "2.53", 
            "start": "172.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When this rotor does a full\nturn, it&#39;ll kick the next", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "174.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "rotor one place.", 
            "dur": "1.65", 
            "start": "177.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then, the right-hand\nrotor keeps going.", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "179.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Eventually, the middle rotor\ndoes a full turn, and it will", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "181.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "kick the left-hand\nrotor one place.", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "184.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So a fast rotor, a middle\nrotor, and a slow rotor.", 
            "dur": "3.49", 
            "start": "186.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Imagine it like it&#39;s hands on\na clock, like you&#39;ve got a", 
            "dur": "2.266", 
            "start": "190.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "minute hand and an hour hand\nand a second hand.", 
            "dur": "1.794", 
            "start": "192.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s the idea.", 
            "dur": "0.94", 
            "start": "194.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Brilliant machine though\nthis is, all it is,", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "195.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "really, is just a circuit.", 
            "dur": "2.47", 
            "start": "197.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here is a battery.", 
            "dur": "0.8", 
            "start": "200.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can see that&#39;s a modern\nbattery in there.", 
            "dur": "1.77", 
            "start": "200.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;ve converted this.", 
            "dur": "1.45", 
            "start": "202.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this battery is connected\nto a bulb.", 
            "dur": "3.69", 
            "start": "204.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it lights up.", 
            "dur": "1.53", 
            "start": "207.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s the most simple thing you\ncan make-- a battery and a", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "209.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bulb, the bulb lights up.", 
            "dur": "1.37", 
            "start": "211.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s all it is.", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "212.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The clever bit is the\nwires of the circuit", 
            "dur": "2.79", 
            "start": "214.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are inside the rotors.", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "217.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So when the wires turn, the\nbattery will connect to a", 
            "dur": "3.85", 
            "start": "219.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "different bulb.", 
            "dur": "0.4", 
            "start": "223.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s try and see that happen.", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "224.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;m going to turn the\nwires, and the battery", 
            "dur": "3.38", 
            "start": "226.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "connects to this bulb.", 
            "dur": "0.99", 
            "start": "229.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Do it again, I&#39;m going to turn\nthe wires, and the battery", 
            "dur": "4.11", 
            "start": "230.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "connects to this bulb.", 
            "dur": "1.23", 
            "start": "234.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It changes.", 
            "dur": "0.85", 
            "start": "236.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Do it again, turn the wires,\nand the battery", 
            "dur": "2.48", 
            "start": "236.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "connects to this bulb.", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "239.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s why it changes each\ntime, because it has moving", 
            "dur": "2.85", 
            "start": "241.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "parts inside.", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "244.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But otherwise, it&#39;s just\na simple circuit.", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "246.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I think we need to know\nhow to decode.", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "248.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This would be no good if we\ncan&#39;t decode our message, so", 
            "dur": "2.645", 
            "start": "250.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let&#39;s do that.", 
            "dur": "0.965", 
            "start": "253.435"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "First of all, we&#39;re going to\ntake our code here, we need to", 
            "dur": "4.04", 
            "start": "254.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "know what the setting was.", 
            "dur": "1.31", 
            "start": "258.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, if you notice, in\nthe little windows,", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "259.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we have three numbers.", 
            "dur": "1.2", 
            "start": "261.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s like a combination lock,\nlike a bike lock.", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "263.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, I took a note of what\nthose three numbers were.", 
            "dur": "3.43", 
            "start": "265.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Those three numbers, when we\nstarted writing Numberphile,", 
            "dur": "3.7", 
            "start": "269.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "were a 13, 9, and 21.", 
            "dur": "5.73", 
            "start": "272.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the idea is, you would type\nin your message, and you would", 
            "dur": "2.59", 
            "start": "278.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "get a code.", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "281.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The machine itself doesn&#39;t\ntransmit, so you would have to", 
            "dur": "2.33", 
            "start": "282.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "write that code on\na piece of paper.", 
            "dur": "2.09", 
            "start": "284.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that piece of paper would be\ngiven to the radio operator", 
            "dur": "3.48", 
            "start": "286.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "who would then transmit\nthe message by", 
            "dur": "1.86", 
            "start": "290.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "radio by Morse code.", 
            "dur": "1.83", 
            "start": "291.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That would travel miles away.", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "293.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So now imagine a second German\nofficer, maybe on a ship", 
            "dur": "3.64", 
            "start": "295.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "somewhere in the ocean,\nnow he&#39;s tuning", 
            "dur": "2.68", 
            "start": "299.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into that radio signal.", 
            "dur": "1.73", 
            "start": "302.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He can hear the code.", 
            "dur": "1.14", 
            "start": "303.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s coming in, and\nhe writes it down.", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "304.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, this second officer\nwill have an", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "307.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Enigma machine as well.", 
            "dur": "1.31", 
            "start": "310.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And his Enigma machine\nis exactly the same", 
            "dur": "2.86", 
            "start": "311.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as the first one.", 
            "dur": "1.44", 
            "start": "314.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there&#39;s something\nI have to do.", 
            "dur": "2.11", 
            "start": "315.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I now need to set these rotors\nto the correct position.", 
            "dur": "2.67", 
            "start": "317.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we&#39;ve got this code over\nhere, Y-T-H-M-Y and whatever.", 
            "dur": "4.64", 
            "start": "320.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s type that into the\nmachine this time", 
            "dur": "1.62", 
            "start": "325.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and see what happens.", 
            "dur": "1.49", 
            "start": "326.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, so we start with Y. Y\nbecomes N. T becomes U. H", 
            "dur": "8.59", 
            "start": "328.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "becomes M. M, in the code, is a\nB. Y. I. F. And W, finally,", 
            "dur": "13.55", 
            "start": "336.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is E. So each rotor has\n26 starting places.", 
            "dur": "6.23", 
            "start": "350.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, these rotors come\nout and swap over.", 
            "dur": "3.63", 
            "start": "356.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, again, they had five\nrotors to pick from.", 
            "dur": "2.85", 
            "start": "360.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They had a box of five rotors.", 
            "dur": "1.82", 
            "start": "363.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You would pick three\nfrom a box of five.", 
            "dur": "2.47", 
            "start": "364.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And already, we&#39;ve got thousands\nof settings.", 
            "dur": "4.85", 
            "start": "367.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And each one will produce\na different code.", 
            "dur": "3.23", 
            "start": "372.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we&#39;re going to work out\nthose combinations.", 
            "dur": "1.87", 
            "start": "375.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the first thing I said was,\nwe pick three rotors from a", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "377.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "box of five.", 
            "dur": "0.87", 
            "start": "380.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the first slot, you would\nhave five rotors to pick from.", 
            "dur": "4.09", 
            "start": "381.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Once you&#39;ve picked that, in the\nsecond place, you would", 
            "dur": "2.96", 
            "start": "385.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "have four rotors to pick from.", 
            "dur": "2.71", 
            "start": "388.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in the final place, the\nthird place, you would have", 
            "dur": "2.49", 
            "start": "391.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "three rotors left.", 
            "dur": "1.75", 
            "start": "393.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And you multiply those\nnumbers together.", 
            "dur": "1.85", 
            "start": "395.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it&#39;s 5 times 4 times 3.", 
            "dur": "1.762", 
            "start": "397.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there are 60 ways that you\ncan put in three rotors from a", 
            "dur": "4.398", 
            "start": "399.022"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "choice of five.", 
            "dur": "1.73", 
            "start": "403.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We have 26 starting positions\nfor each rotor.", 
            "dur": "3.26", 
            "start": "405.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we have 26 choices for the\nfirst one, 26 choices for the", 
            "dur": "3.99", 
            "start": "408.41"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "second one, and 26 choices\nfor the third one.", 
            "dur": "3.52", 
            "start": "412.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if you do that, you get\n26 cubed, which is 17,576.", 
            "dur": "5.74", 
            "start": "415.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It gets worse, because the\nmilitary, the Army, Air Force,", 
            "dur": "4.19", 
            "start": "421.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Navy had something extra.", 
            "dur": "2.97", 
            "start": "425.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The commercial machines--", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "428.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if you were a bank or a\nbusiness, you could buy an", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "429.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Enigma machine to use yourself\nto send your own secrets.", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "431.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But the military had\nan extra bit.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "435.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They had this thing at the\nfront of the machine.", 
            "dur": "2.62", 
            "start": "437.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, this is called\na plugboard.", 
            "dur": "1.71", 
            "start": "439.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s like an old-fashioned\ntelephone switchboard, like an", 
            "dur": "4.26", 
            "start": "441.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "old patchboard.", 
            "dur": "1.36", 
            "start": "445.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We have 10 of these wires.", 
            "dur": "3.72", 
            "start": "447.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And each of these wires\nconnect two", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "450.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "letters into a pair.", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "453.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So in this case, you might see,\nthe letter Q is going to", 
            "dur": "4.04", 
            "start": "455.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "connect with the letter E. Now\nyou make 10 of those pairs.", 
            "dur": "5.4", 
            "start": "459.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Two letters in a pair\nwill swap over.", 
            "dur": "3.04", 
            "start": "464.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if Q is connected to E, then\nQ and E would swap over.", 
            "dur": "4.14", 
            "start": "468.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s an extra level of\nscrambling only available to", 
            "dur": "3.36", 
            "start": "472.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the military.", 
            "dur": "0.66", 
            "start": "475.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, this had the most number\nof combinations.", 
            "dur": "4.65", 
            "start": "476.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, this calculation is going\nto be the hardest calculation,", 
            "dur": "2.53", 
            "start": "480.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but we can do it.", 
            "dur": "1.59", 
            "start": "483.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there are 26 letters\nin the alphabet.", 
            "dur": "2.69", 
            "start": "484.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How many ways to arrange\n26 letters?", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "487.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, it&#39;s 26 times 25 times\n24 all the way down to 1.", 
            "dur": "4.16", 
            "start": "490.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s 26 factorial.", 
            "dur": "1.65", 
            "start": "494.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But we don&#39;t want every\ncombination of 26 letters.", 
            "dur": "3.43", 
            "start": "496.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We only want to make 10 pairs.", 
            "dur": "1.44", 
            "start": "499.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that means there are 6\nletters left over, which we", 
            "dur": "2.56", 
            "start": "500.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "don&#39;t care about.", 
            "dur": "1.42", 
            "start": "503.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because we don&#39;t care about\nthem, that means", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "504.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we&#39;re allowed to divide.", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "506.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we&#39;re going to divide\nby 6 factorial.", 
            "dur": "3.4", 
            "start": "508.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now there are 10 pairs.", 
            "dur": "1.71", 
            "start": "512.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We don&#39;t care what order\nthose 10 pairs are in.", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "513.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because we don&#39;t care\nabout it, we can", 
            "dur": "1.35", 
            "start": "517.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "divide by 10 factorial.", 
            "dur": "3.78", 
            "start": "518.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the last thing to divide\nby, 2 letters in a pair.", 
            "dur": "3.94", 
            "start": "522.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, if I swap them\nover, that would", 
            "dur": "2.38", 
            "start": "526.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "still be the same pair.", 
            "dur": "1.18", 
            "start": "528.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If I had A and B, that&#39;s the\nsame as B and A. That&#39;s still", 
            "dur": "3.32", 
            "start": "529.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the same pair.", 
            "dur": "1.04", 
            "start": "533.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I can divide by 2.", 
            "dur": "1.48", 
            "start": "534.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I do that for each pair.", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "535.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There&#39;s 10 pairs, so I&#39;m going\nto divide by 2 10 times.", 
            "dur": "5.68", 
            "start": "537.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just 2 to power 10.", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "543.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that is how many ways that\nyou can connect 20 letters", 
            "dur": "5.29", 
            "start": "545.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into 10 pairs on the front\nof the machine.", 
            "dur": "2.55", 
            "start": "550.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How big is that number?", 
            "dur": "0.58", 
            "start": "553.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Shall we do that?", 
            "dur": "1.054", 
            "start": "553.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "150 trillion, 738 billion,\n274 million, 937,250.", 
            "dur": "14.546", 
            "start": "554.824"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the total, 158 quintillion,\n962 quadrillion, 555 trillion,", 
            "dur": "12.43", 
            "start": "569.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "217 billion, 826 million,\n360,000 flat.", 
            "dur": "12.46", 
            "start": "581.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That is the total number of\nways that you can set the", 
            "dur": "2.78", 
            "start": "594.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Enigma machine.", 
            "dur": "1.04", 
            "start": "597.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This would be an army Enigma\nmachine around about 1939.", 
            "dur": "3.45", 
            "start": "598.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "-You are telling me that the\nGermans would send each other", 
            "dur": "2.93", 
            "start": "601.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "messages like Numberphile\nor send--", 
            "dur": "2.84", 
            "start": "604.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: Yeah, they\ndid that all the time.", 
            "dur": "1.23", 
            "start": "607.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "-Or send the U-boat to this\nposition or whatever.", 
            "dur": "4.26", 
            "start": "608.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But how were they telling each\nother their plug settings and", 
            "dur": "3.69", 
            "start": "612.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "their starting rotor numbers?", 
            "dur": "1.19", 
            "start": "616.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: So this\nis very important.", 
            "dur": "1.68", 
            "start": "617.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So these two people, who are\nmiles apart, need to have the", 
            "dur": "2.79", 
            "start": "619.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "same setting.", 
            "dur": "1.01", 
            "start": "622.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, the setting was written\ndown for you", 
            "dur": "2.27", 
            "start": "623.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on a piece of paper.", 
            "dur": "1.29", 
            "start": "625.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What they would have is a sheet\nof paper like that.", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "626.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it would be a big\nsheet of paper for", 
            "dur": "2.77", 
            "start": "629.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "each day of the month.", 
            "dur": "1.73", 
            "start": "632.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it was a monthly sheet.", 
            "dur": "1.67", 
            "start": "634.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For each day of the month, they\ntold you how to set the", 
            "dur": "2.43", 
            "start": "636.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "machine for that day.", 
            "dur": "1.52", 
            "start": "638.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you didn&#39;t have this sheet\nof paper, you wouldn&#39;t know", 
            "dur": "3.25", 
            "start": "640.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what the setting was that you\nhad to use for that day.", 
            "dur": "4", 
            "start": "643.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And nice, little story, the Navy\nwould write these code", 
            "dur": "2.95", 
            "start": "647.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "books in soluble ink.", 
            "dur": "1.41", 
            "start": "650.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if you get sunk, if you get\ncaught, if you throw the code", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "651.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "book into water, that&#39;s how\nyou keep the secret.", 
            "dur": "2.695", 
            "start": "654.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "-It sounds to me that all you\nneed is an Enigma machine and", 
            "dur": "4.035", 
            "start": "657.535"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a copy of that book,\nand you know", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "661.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "everything they&#39;re saying.", 
            "dur": "0.67", 
            "start": "664.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: You would do.", 
            "dur": "0.78", 
            "start": "664.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if you had the machine and\nyou had that code sheet, you", 
            "dur": "4.13", 
            "start": "665.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would be able to decode\nall the messages.", 
            "dur": "2.19", 
            "start": "669.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Fantastic.", 
            "dur": "0.72", 
            "start": "672"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Great.", 
            "dur": "1.12", 
            "start": "672.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But we had the machine.", 
            "dur": "2.68", 
            "start": "673.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And once we&#39;ve had the machine,\nwe can pull it apart", 
            "dur": "2.19", 
            "start": "676.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and find out how it works.", 
            "dur": "1.01", 
            "start": "678.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Great.", 
            "dur": "0.9", 
            "start": "679.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But it was getting those\ncode sheets.", 
            "dur": "2.26", 
            "start": "680.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That was difficult.", 
            "dur": "1.1", 
            "start": "682.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They were monthly.", 
            "dur": "0.81", 
            "start": "683.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They would change every month.", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "684.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you did capture them, which\nwe did occasionally, you could", 
            "dur": "3.86", 
            "start": "686.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "use it until it runs out.", 
            "dur": "1.74", 
            "start": "690.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But without a code sheet, you\nwould have to break the code.", 
            "dur": "3.76", 
            "start": "691.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And you would have to do\nthat with mathematics.", 
            "dur": "1.1", 
            "start": "695.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "-What was the key?", 
            "dur": "1.615", 
            "start": "696.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What was wrong with Enigma?", 
            "dur": "1.185", 
            "start": "698.245"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What was its weakness?", 
            "dur": "0.975", 
            "start": "699.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "DR. JAMES GRIME: Let&#39;s have a\nlook at what the flaw is in", 
            "dur": "3.11", 
            "start": "700.405"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the Enigma machine.", 
            "dur": "1.165", 
            "start": "703.515"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the Germans thought\nit was unbreakable,", 
            "dur": "2.13", 
            "start": "704.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but there is a flaw.", 
            "dur": "1.41", 
            "start": "706.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If I press a letter K--", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "708.22"
        }
